cpu-cooler-lcd (1.1-1) unstable; urgency=medium

  * Tray icon now starts the controller service automatically and only
    shows while the service is running.
  * Replaced "Quit Tray Icon" with "Unload Everything" in the tray menu.
  * Settings GUI now starts the controller service and tray icon if
    they aren't already running.

 -- Paul Lintott <paul.lintott@gmail.com>  Fri, 12 Jun 2026 06:00:00 +0000

cpu-cooler-lcd (1.0-1) unstable; urgency=medium

  * Initial Debian packaging.
  * Made config and device-layout file paths relocatable
    (~/.config/cpu-cooler-lcd, /usr/share/cpu-cooler-lcd) so the app can
    run from a system install instead of the source tree.
  * Added "Restart Tray Icon" and "Unload Everything" buttons to the
    settings GUI.
  * Added an application icon.
  * Fixed a crash in CPU power reading on systems without RAPL support.

 -- Paul Lintott <paul.lintott@gmail.com>  Thu, 11 Jun 2026 21:00:00 +0000
